CALCULATING EXPONENTS WITH LOOPS
--------------------------------------------------
This program will calculate basic integer exponents like 2^10 for example.
--------------------------------------------------

1) Declare the integers base, exponent, and result
2) Assign 1 to result
3) Assign some test values for base and exponent (ex: 2 5)
5) Write a loop that runs if and only if exponent is greater than zero
6) In the body of the loop, assign the product of result times base to result
7) In the body of the loop, subtract 1 from exponent
8) Once the loop completes, print "solution is [value of solution]"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

PART II - Functionality
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Modify the program so that it uses real numbers instead of discrete numbers.
Test if 2.5^2 works as expected.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

PART III - Optimization
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Replace the while loop with a for loop and eliminate the exponent variable
